questions.t:
A developer wants to shorten this code:
function multiply(a, b) {
  return a*b;
}
Which modern JavaScript feature is BEST suited for this purpose?

What is the output of the following code?

let x = -2;
if (x > 0) {
  console.log("Positive");
} else if (x < 0) {
  console.log("Negative");
} else {
  console.log("Zero");
}

What is the output of:

const x = (x, y) => x * y;
console.log(x(2,3))

What is the output of the following code?

let x = 10;
if (x > 5) {
  console.log("Positive");
}

What is the output of the following code?

let x = 7;
if (x % 2 == 0) {
  console.log("Even");
} else {
  console.log("Odd");
}

What is the output of the following code?

for (let i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}

